{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cataracts/diagnosis/clinical-features/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"ca1cc737-768b-5a84-a145-fccedb1afcc5","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 798e8b6e-ef8b-481c-9c85-ab6d0099ef9f --><h2>What are the clinical features of cataracts?</h2><!-- end field 798e8b6e-ef8b-481c-9c85-ab6d0099ef9f -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item e6241742-74c2-4cad-adea-ab6d0099ef3a --><!-- begin field 508f4328-4579-4755-9391-ab6d0099efa0 --><ul><li><strong>The main symptom of cataract is a gradual and painless reduction in visual clarity and sharpness. </strong></li><li><strong>People with cataracts experience:</strong><ul><li>Reduced acuity.</li><li>Blurred vision. </li><li>Difficulty seeing at night. </li><li>Difficulty reading text.</li><li>Sensitivity to light and glare. </li><li>'Halos' around lights and double vision in a single eye.</li><li>Polyopia (multiple images). </li><li>Frequent changes of spectacle prescription as a result of cataracts developing. </li><li>Difficulty recognizing faces. </li><li>Problems watching television. </li><li>Gradual reduction in perception of colour intensity (especially blues). </li></ul></li><li><strong>Signs and s</strong><strong>ymptoms of cataracts </strong>in children include:<ul><li>Poor vision — parents/carers may suspect the child does not have good vision because the child may not notice them or does not follow objects with their eyes. Visual acuity may be tested in older children.</li><li>A white or grey pupil (leukocoria) — this may be seen by the naked eye or when examined by an ophthalmoscope.</li><li>Involuntary eye movements (nystagmus). </li><li>Squint (strabismus). </li><li>Sensitivity to light or problems with glare (the child may close the affected eye to ward off glare).</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 508f4328-4579-4755-9391-ab6d0099efa0 --><!-- end item e6241742-74c2-4cad-adea-ab6d0099ef3a -->","topic":{"id":"eeb34712-def5-5b38-9125-fec8925c1bcc","topicId":"9a3fe0f5-1b06-4ff6-9a79-2ed4a8f4b2c5","topicName":"Cataracts","slug":"cataracts","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"90f4d5e6-8dee-54a2-b535-a3280c9ff7e9","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"da1f4019-d02d-523b-80ce-e4ba8579b43d","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"87a3b79a-dbff-50b1-a10c-fc54f60080f3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"cd79c0cf-e5a8-5fb6-99af-3d9e0eaf4b28","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"d0c360ad-3631-54ab-809e-570769cd5aa1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"8af6938b-ae1b-5c2a-8b8c-826edbed8669","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed0ddb2-07a6-5c9e-86b8-740894cd88e7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d3db836f-68b9-5c32-bb04-1d6c9b755015","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"78ff1c73-3038-544d-829b-9c4fa6e07ea0","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"656fb8f7-2abd-5f0f-ad42-29abf4c1f6f6","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"b62da534-cf57-5fe0-b8ab-b615d0f453db","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"aeadf6c4-c840-5132-8088-24333b53ef51","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"72d37d02-73ec-5804-8b0b-ec8c9f598bd8","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"7c9d7f21-34f0-5df8-a1d4-8826a0ace32c","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"0a895e5e-b9bb-54b2-9872-590fc78989e5","slug":"causes-risk-factors","fullItemName":"Causes/risk factors"},{"id":"79a1f298-b9fa-5e1