ces","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"e87190fb-3f26-5832-b880-cec44fe6b479","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"a35f7ed6-69d9-5da4-a920-d49372a86c91","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-465","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c3249aff-378d-48d9-90b0-ab6e00f0bd9f --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field c3249aff-378d-48d9-90b0-ab6e00f0bd9f -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 4657a6be-4a71-444b-97f8-ab6e00f0bce5 --><!-- begin field f891e126-c13c-47b6-a6e1-ab6e00f0bd9f --><p>This information is based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline <em>Cataracts in adults: management</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>], the British Medical Journal (BMJ) best practice guide <em>Cataracts</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>], expert opinion in a medical textbook <em>ABC of eyes </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Khaw, 2004</a>], and expert opinion in narrative reviews <em>Care of older adults: role of primary care physicians in the treatment of cataracts and macular degeneration</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Marra, 2016</a>], <em>Cataract and surgery for cataract</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Allen and Vasavada, 2006</a>], <em>Congenital cataract</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Russell et al, 2011</a>], and <em>Paediatric cataract: challenges and future direction</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Medsinge and Nischal, 2015